CCD-3011 PATTERNS (MHz) Newton with LTC2207 A/D
-----------------
This pattern uses the 4H channel with 4 speeds of 5MHz, 3MHz, 1MHz and 50kHz.
Sequence is I3, I1, I2, I3 down towards the shift reg.
Image 3 is last row before shift reg.
Charge is transfered into R1 and R2 with R3 aligned with channel stops.
Sequence is: ...R3, R1, R2, R3, OG, Node
S1 to S4	Storage area clks
I1 to I4	Image area clks
B	Engine branch bit
SB1 to SB4	Engine loop speed bits. (Not applicable to Vertical Shift Routines) 
               For n = 0 Hold = 1; 
               For 0 to n to 8 Hold = (2^(n-1)) + 1;
               For n to 8   Hold = (256*(n-1))+1;
RST	CCD reset
PEN            KHz Sample clock used specifically for MAX1133ACAP A/D (Not used on New Newton Platform)
HVF	EMCCD HV falling edge (Only applicable on CCD-207 sensors)
AMP	Input amp restore
DSR            KHz Dual Slope Integrator Reset Pulse (Not used on New Newton Platform)
HVR	EMCCD HV rising edge (Only applicable on CCD-207 sensors)
CDS	Clamp to Ground	
R1 to R3	Horz register clks
MUX	Mux between analog channels
DSP            KHz Dual Slope Integrator Positive Pulse (Not used on New Newton Platform)
FIR	FIRE engine output - This is overwritten by software
DSN            KHz Dual Slope Integrator Negative Pulse (Not used on New Newton Platform)
PA1            Pre amp gain 1 overide
FRA	FRAME engine output - This is overwritten by software
RS	Reset sample (D-CDS)
SS	Signal sample (D-CDS); USB keep quiet
OSK	OS kill (stop CCD output amp glow) - Switches VOD off
CG2	Clamp-to-ground on analog channel 2 (Not used on Newton)
PA2	Pre amp gain 2 overide
PXL	Valid output pixel clk (Not used on New Newton Platform)
SW	Summing well clk (Not Used on Newton as this is simply fed with R3 Clock)
SHU            SHUTTER engine output - This is overwritten by software
SSK            VSS Kill - Switches VSS OFF

-----------------

Turning off horz clocks during exposure at higher speeds to
stop 'background dark signal' and 'glow'.

P01 - First Pattern for 30-11 sensor in Newton platform with new LTC2207 A/D - Based on P07z40P_4H CS 21/05/09
P02 - Pattern file uses original Newton Vertical Shift Patterns to maintain Vertical Shift Speed Options 28/07/09 
P03 - Pattern uses original VH and HV routines and 1MHz tweaked to reduce curl. 
      Also, 3MHz tweaked to make Reference stable during exposure to light. CS 22/10/09 
P04 - 3MHz pattern reduced to 27 lines to achieve readout speed of 2.96MHz CS 22/10/09
P05 - HS-RD-CLK routine changed for 1MHz readout to remove first column deviation CS 17/11/09
